Clearly the intuition is to some how find the distances(shortest) from node 1 and node 2 to all other nodes and then compare the node distances from node1 and node2 where it can smaller and return that node.
So first approach of finding shortest disatnce to all other nodes comes to our mind is bfs or dijkstra's algo (mostly used algofor these kind of problems). So simply do bfs or dijkstra separately from node1 and node2 and store the distances in respective vectors and then comapare all the nodes form 0 to n-1 where max distance is minimum and return that node. This is compeletely the first approach of this problem then we can further find some shorter solutions as well but understanding is only this.
